comment.body:
These indexes make no sense to me.   Don't we always query by `peer_party_id` first, and then `timestamp` and then `timestamp_discriminator` ?  The order of these columns is critically important.

I would expect:

```
<column name="peer_party_id"/>
<column name="timestamp"/>
<column name="timestamp_discriminator"/>
<column name="transaction_id"/>
```

pull_request.body:
I have some corresponding ENT changes that always use batching when in recovery mode, and thus always use FetchBatchTransactionsFlow.

Have verified forwards / backwards compatibility of serialisation / deserialisation of `MaybeSerializedSignedTransaction`
